## Before writing any styles

1. Read `src/styles.scss` — reuse existing `:root` tokens before creating new ones.
2. Check `src/app/shared/` for a composable component and `src/styles.scss` for an existing engine (`.c-button`, `.c-card`, `.c-chip`, `.c-dropdown`). Prefer reuse.

## Three-Tier Token Rule

| Tier | When | Where |
|------|------|-------|
| **Global** | Value used across multiple components | `src/styles.scss` `:root { --name: value; }` → use `var(--name)` everywhere |
| **Component-scoped** | Value reused only inside this file | `:host { --local: value; }` → use `var(--local)` only here |
| **No token** | Value used once or twice | Write the value directly — no variable needed |

Use `var(--token)` and `rem`/`em` in rule bodies. Hex/px only inside `:root` or `:host` token definitions.

## Five-Group Vertical Rhythm (mandatory)

Every selector MUST group properties into these five blocks, separated by **one blank line**. Omit empty groups.

```scss
.selector {
  /* 1 — Layout */
  display: flex;
  position: relative;
  align-items: center;

  /* 2 — Dimensions */
  width: 100%;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  gap: 0.5rem;

  /* 3 — Content / Typography */
  background-color: var(--bg-primary);
  color: var(--text-primary);
  font-size: 0.875rem;

  /* 4 — Structure */
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  overflow: hidden;

  /* 5 — Effects */
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: filter 0.2s ease;
}
```

Group order: Layout → Dimensions → Content/Typo → Structure → Effects.

## Per-Selector Checklist

- [ ] Can I reuse an existing engine (`.c-*`) or `shared/` component?
- [ ] Did I check `src/styles.scss` and pick the right token tier?
- [ ] Are properties sorted into the 5 groups with blank lines between?
- [ ] Are values using `var(--)` and `rem`/`em` where a token applies?
- [ ] No `style="..."` attributes — zero inline styles.

